\title{LibeRation: population PK/PD modelling with a C++ runtime}
\description{
NONMEM-compatible population PK/PD model specification, simulation, estimation, diagnostics, and graphical workflow management with one C++ numerical runtime. Implements ADVAN1-4, ADVAN6, ADVAN11-13, arbitrary linear matrix propagation, analytical and nonlinear periodic steady state, exact automatic differentiation, thirteen population estimation methods, declarative continuous, categorical, count, event-time, competing-risk, arbitrary-state continuous-time and observed/hidden Markov and semi-Markov likelihoods, correlated joint endpoints, generalized nested/crossed random effects, ARMA residual processes, nonlinear EKF/UKF and particle state-space inference, and continuous-discrete stochastic differential equations. Also provides filtering, retrospective smoothing, stochastic simulation, diagnostics, advanced editable ODE templates, and versioned projects. Models use the established LibeRation R syntax or the restricted C++ expression form.
